SwiftUI work for Vocello macOS and iOS.

## Architecture

- iOS: preserve `@Observable` + `AppModel`; no `@StateObject` / `@Published` for new code
- iOS design tokens align to macOS (May 2026) — check macOS values before changing colors, glass, radii
- Liquid Glass: `@available(iOS 26, *)` + Reduce Transparency solid fallbacks

## Recommended Axiom agents

| Change type | `subagent_type` |
|---|---|
| Feature / refactor | `swiftui-architecture-auditor` |
| Jank / slow render | `swiftui-performance-analyzer` |
| Glass / tint / radius | `liquid-glass-auditor` |
| Sheets / tabs / empty states | `ux-flow-auditor` |
| Layout / iPad | `swiftui-layout-auditor` |
| Navigation / deep links | `swiftui-nav-auditor` |

Skills: `build-ios-apps:swiftui-ui-patterns`, `axiom:axiom-swiftui`, `build-macos-apps:swiftui-patterns` as needed.

## Testing

- iOS Simulator: stub MLX only — see [`docs/reference/ios-simulator-testing.md`](../../docs/reference/ios-simulator-testing.md)
- Real MLX on iPhone: `./scripts/ios_device.sh` — not Simulator proof for performance

## Picker menus

Drive by **keyboard** (`Down` / `Up` / `Return`), not fixed menu-item coordinates — see [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md).

